  "chapter": {
    "number": 62,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "Zion’s Salvation and New Name"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For Zion’s sake I will not keep silent,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and for Jerusalem’s sake I will not keep still,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "until her righteousness shines like a bright light,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "her salvation like a blazing torch.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Nations will see your righteousness,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and all kings your glory.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "You will be called by a new name",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "that the mouth of the LORD will bestow.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "You will be a crown of glory in the hand of the LORD,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "a royal diadem in the palm of your God.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "No longer will you be called Forsaken,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2733
          },
          {
            "text": "nor your land named Desolate;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2734
          },
          {
            "text": "but you will be called Hephzibah,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2735
          },
          {
            "text": "and your land Beulah;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2736
          },
          {
            "text": "for the LORD will take delight in you,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and your land will be His bride.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For as a young man marries a young woman,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "so your sons will marry you;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and as a bridegroom rejoices over his bride,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "so your God will rejoice over you.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "On your walls, O Jerusalem, I have posted watchmen;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "they will never be silent day or night.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "You who call on the LORD",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "shall take no rest for yourselves,",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 7,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "nor give Him any rest",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "until He establishes Jerusalem",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and makes her the praise of the earth.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 8,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The LORD has sworn by His right hand",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and by His mighty arm:",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "“Never again will I give your grain",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "to your enemies for food,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "nor will foreigners drink the new wine",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "for which you have toiled.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 9,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For those who harvest grain",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "will eat it and praise the LORD,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and those who gather grapes",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "will drink the wine in My holy courts.”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 10,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Go out, go out through the gates;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "prepare the way for the people!",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Build it up, build up the highway;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "clear away the stones;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "raise a banner for the nations!",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 11,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Behold, the LORD has proclaimed",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "to the ends of the earth,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "“Say to Daughter Zion:",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "See, your Savior comes!",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Look, His reward is with Him,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and His recompense goes before Him.”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 12,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "And they will be called the Holy People,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the Redeemed of The LORD;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and you will be called Sought Out,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "A City Not Forsaken.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
    "footnotes": [
